==English==

===Noun===
'''jibe'''  (''plural:'' '''[[jibes]]''')
# A [[facetious]] or [[insult]]ing remark, a [[jeer]] or [[taunt]] eg. block head, in reference to Robert Jones (Form 10A, The Marches School and Technology College, Oswestry) due to the fact that he has an exceptionally square shaped head.
# (''nautical'') A manoeuver in which the [[stern]] of a sailing [[boat]] or [[ship]] crosses the [[wind]].
# (''nautical'') (of a sail) to suddenly sweep across from one side of the boat to the other.

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|jib|e|}}
# To perform a jibe (2, 3).
# To agree.  (''That explanation doesn't jibe with the facts.'') 

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|jib|e|}}
# To cause to execute a jibe (2, 3).

